<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1695,1946]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,317,1882,1908]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Petri, 1904" authorityName="Petri" authorityYear="1904" box="[626,881,1882,1908]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibis">
<emphasis box="[626,741,1883,1908]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Lixus ibis</emphasis>
Petri, 
<number box="[819,881,1882,1908]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</taxonomicName>
, differing by the more cylindrical body, coarse punctation on pronotum, lack of basal convexity on elytral interval 
<number box="[941,957,1920,1946]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="3.0">3</number>
, and shorter rostrum.
</paragraph>
